	<p><font size="2" face="Verdana, Arial">First of all I would like to thank for your update and the live team and the testers in doing so many work in trying to balance out the cleric class. I really appreciate it.<br />
<br />
Some of my thoughts:<br />
<br />
1. At this stage so far, its seems that the balancing is more oriented to give cleric the ability to melee to cause damage. How the live team come up with this decision? Do the cleric community really like this change or they actually prefer to cause damage by nuking?<br />
<br />
2. The spells addition are nice but only 58+ cleric will benefit from it. Level 54 - 58 clerics will be the most affected group with the changes currently on test. The coming changes seems have nothing to help them to add value to groups. <br />
<br />
3. "In testing, clerics have been effective soloing the entrance to Charasis and Chardok, grouping in a number of high end dungeons, and even making reasonable experience as a two-cleric duo in Cazic-Thule."<br />
Are these level 60 clerics? I hope not, otherwise the 54-58 clerics will not be benefit from the change.<br />
<br />
4. The "solo" hammer is a neat interesting idea. However, don't you think that the cleric class will be too dependant on a single weapon?  It will mean that I can't use my hard-earned nice 2hb when I have to go solo?<br />
<br />
I understand that changes is not yet completed. The above is only my observatiion/opinion so far about the direction of the changes<br />
