<tr>
	<td bgcolor="#F7F7F7" width="175" valign="top" nowrap>
	<a name="post101667"></a>
	
	<font size="2" face="Verdana, Arial"><b>Niin</b></font><br>
	<font size="1" face="Verdana, Arial">Cleric</font><br>
	<p>
	<font size="1" face="Verdana, Arial">Registered: Nov 1999<br>
	Location: <br>
	Posts: 23</font></td>
	
	<td bgcolor="#F7F7F7" width="100%" valign="top">
	<font size="1" face="Verdana, Arial"> <b></b></font>
	<p><font size="2" face="Verdana, Arial">I appreciate you coming to give us this update.  But I can't let this one go:<br />
<br />
"Other supporting spells available to the cleric are his low cost summoned pet, and the Mark of Retribution/Mark of Karn spells"<br />
<br />
You do realize that Mark of Karn is only useful do get rid of mob damage shields?  That the amount it heals is so ultimiately trivial that it doesn't justify its cost?  And that the casting time on the Velious BPs is so long that the combat is over by the time we're done casting the spell, only to have it resisted?<br />
<br />
You cannot honestly tell me that Mark of Karn is useful in any way, other than it being a 'targeted dispel' for damage shields.<br />
<br />
"Using Yaulp + the Hammer of Judgement, the cleric begins to be effective in toe-to-toe combat"<br />
<br />
Um, maybe in terms of melee damage, but not in terms of damage taken.  I have one of the higher ACs/HPs (1250 AC, 4100 hps with self buffs) for clerics on our server, and mobs completely own me in toe-to-toe combat.   Even high green mobs hit for max like every other swing.<br />
<br />
Not to mention, did you bother to even ASK if clerics actually WANTED to be bad paladins?  Most clerics do not; just read this forum.<br />
<br />
I would much rather see this 'improved benefit for groups' be more along the lines of actually improving our support role, the role that I have had for the 3+ years I've played EQ.  Make clerics make the *group* better in some way.  Give new/different Mark type spells; give 'bard-like' abilities to up melee stats of your entire party, or improve mana regen somewhat.<br />
<br />
You, Verant, have defined what a cleric was for the past 3 years; those that actually still play the class (as opposed to probably half the clerics out there now days being 2-boxed) play it because they love the SUPPORTING role.  <br />
<br />
If I wanted to be a paladin, I'd have started a paladin.<br />
<br />
There are many cleric-only weapons out there; or weapons that are often given to clerics.  Instead of making a summoned hammer, which completely negates ALL WEAPONS FOR CLERICS IN THE GAME, make the 'hammer' proc instead a buff that adds a melee proc (much like Divine Might for paladins).  That would allow clerics to choose the weapon *they* want to use, and still get this added proc benefit you seem to be claiming will solve all our problems.</font></p>
	
	<p></p>
	<p><font size="1" face="Verdana, Arial"><i>Last edited by Niin on 08-23-2002 at 12:42 PM</i></font></p>
