	<td bgcolor="#DEDFDF" width="100%" valign="top">
	<font size="1" face="Verdana, Arial"> <b></b></font>
	<p><font size="2" face="Verdana, Arial">Must be the late hours and lack of sleep that cooked up these "upgrades" to the Cleric class.  <br />
<br />
Where are the Def skills that are going to keep clerics alive while all this melee'ing is going on and we're getting hit for doubles and trip's of 120+   Or are the new summoned weapons going to generate ZERO agro in a group situation so we dont get our beat down from all these frequent proc's and have to take a rez from a passing Necro or Pally?  oh maybe thats why we need more than one cleric in a group now.<br />
<br />
We get to kill a Dragon in WW now?  <br />
<br />
We get to snare and quad with ranged AE spells?  blue cons?<br />
<br />
We get a Epic weapon thats practically contention free and the final mob is triggered on demand?  Ohhhh wait, we dont need that anymore, we are now Pally-Mages (WOOHOO!! the first dual class in EQ) and we're gonna SUMMON our new MELEE weapon.<br />
<br />
Clerics have been using this at zone in at Charsis and Chardok huh?  Well I am overwhelmed.   2 zone in's where you have to have Invis to get to and at least in Chardok you can DB (oh yeah, dont mem that anymore, need the slot for Yaulp V, thx~) to zone OUT when it goes bad.  Hope nobody is camping the fort or Zone out, they gonna be in big trouble when I train their butts to hell and gone. <br />
<br />
As for Charisis, just how do you suppose I'm gonna get my corpse back if/when it goes bad, mem up my new improved pet hammer?  Zone requires Invis just to get to, cant bind outside like Sebilis unless you are on good terms with Venril Sathir which your about to destroy for going inside and to top it all off, after we BUY or BEG a port to Skyfire we get to run KoS through 2 zones.  Zone into a hot landing zone where mobs HT for ~650 points, but this is okay because you have seen it work on Test Server once, and it only worked in these zones because it's the only place in the game where low blues can be single pulled that happens to allow us to mem up a couple of our truly useable offensive spells, Undead nukes and dots.<br />
<br />
GO BACK TO THE DRAWING BOARDS!  These fixes dont fix anything.  You guys are proving you know exactly jack and squat about clerics, priest classes in general and what their current capabilities are, what these changes will do, and what game balance is.  <br />
<br />
Fix healing by giving Druids a group heal that can be used often enough to mitigate AE's from boss mobs, a nice phat heal for them that is much higher than 400 mana would do also, the new Druid CH is fine at 10 seconds but bump it to 600 mana.  Why the heck should they get the same cast time, the same mana cost and the same amount of HP's healed?  go parse a clerics CH logs sometime.  Not a raiding cleric from one of the top 3 guilds on a server that makes 5% or less of the cleric population, Joe Avg Cleric, see what his CH's hit for.... SURPRISE!!!  Same amount of hitpoints.  Roughly 3k unless he is letting the tank get near dead.</font></p>
	
